<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3335] Exception while evaluating classes with static toString() methods</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3335</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Try the following script:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;assert &apos;class java.text.SimpleDateFormat&apos; == java.text.SimpleDateFormat.toString()&lt;br/&gt;
assert &apos;class java.lang.Integer&apos; == java.lang.Integer.toString()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the second statement throws exception:&lt;br/&gt;
Exception thrown: Could not find which method toString() to invoke from this list:&lt;br/&gt;
  public static java.lang.String java.lang.Integer#toString(int)&lt;br/&gt;
  public static java.lang.String java.lang.Integer#toString(int, int)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like Class.toString() is not taken into account while trying to evaluate this expression.&lt;br/&gt;
Integer.class.toString() produces the same error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
